s use Taskei link\ncti.amazon.com\n| user/LOGIN/ctis - CTI and resolver groups of specific user\n| user/LOGIN/groups - resolver group membership of specific user\n| group/RESOLVER_GROUP/ctis - CTI assignments of resolver group\n| cti/ctis?category=CATEGORY&type=TYPE&item=ITEM - searches CTIs by category type and item\nsage.amazon.dev\n| posts/POST_ID\n| tags/TAG_NAME?page=N - details and questions of specific Sage tag, default page 1\nobserve.aka.amazon.com/carnaval/\n| ?searchQuery=SEARCH_STRING - search Carnaval alarms\n| alarm/ALARM_NAME - alarm details\n| alarm/history/ALARM_NAME - alarm history\nmeetings.amazon.com - rooms can be email or name, example SEA54-03.101; use requester TZ; determine requester location with phone tool\n| calendar/find/LOGIN?startTime=ISO_DATE&endTime=ISO_DATE - get calendar events, 8AM-6PM default for single day\n| calendar/get/ENTRY?alias=LOGIN - get full calendar event details based on ENTRY and alias\n| rooms/find/BUILDING - search meeting rooms by building like SEA54 or URI encoded name like Nitro%20North. Options floor=N, minCapacity=N, availability=true with startTime=ISO_DATE&endTime=ISO_DATE\n| rooms/availability?rooms=ROOM1,ROOM2&startTime=ISO_DATE&endTime=ISO_DATE - room availability\nconsensus.a2z.com - approval tool where users create CAZ reviews and ask others to approve\n| reviews - list user reviews\n| reviews/REVIEW_ID\nconsole.cams.ops.amazon.dev Contingent Authorization Metadata Service CAMS manages create update read of resource specific metadata for contingent authorization CAZ evaluation\n| / list all resource classifications\n| /resource-classification/ID get resource classification\nisengard.amazon.com/manage-accounts/\n| / List AWS accounts with user access: ownership, bindles & auth details\n| ACCOUNT_ID/manage - Get AWS Account overview including owernership, bindle information, CAZ status\nrome.aws.dev\n| / retrieve user owned services and ids AAA:Internal Amazon security framework for authentication and aut